H0.text: What name is given to a positive whole number that can only be divided by 1 or itself. Primeval

H1.text: What name is given to a positive whole number that can only be divided by 1 or itself. Monic

H2.text: What name is given to a positive whole number that can only be divided by 1 or itself. Elemental

H3.text: What name is given to a positive whole number that can only be divided by 1 or itself. ℙ

A4.text: A prime number (or a prime) is a natural number greater than 1 that is not a product of two smaller natural numbers.

A5.text: jing the set of all primes is sometimes denoted by P or by ℙ
